e now</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>edos-builddebcheck (shipped in the <a href=\"http://packages.debian.org/sid/edos-debcheck\">same package</a>),\nwhich is a wrapper around edos-debcheck (by coincidence, developed\nat last year's DebConf by me and Ralf Treinen) which checks for\n<strong>installability of build dependencies</strong></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Just yesterday <a href=\"https://www.joachim-breitner.de/blog/\">nomeata</a> tortured\n<a href=\"http://packages.debian.org/sid/devel/wanna-build\">wanna-build</a>\nto integrate edos-builddebcheck into it. That way,\n<strong>wanna-build</strong> will discover in advance whether a\npackage is <strong>unbuildable due to uninstallable\nbuild-deps</strong>; if this is the case, the package will be put\nin a new state (which will be rechecked at archive change) without\nbothering the buildd maintainer.</p>\n<p>Very cool, thanks nomeata!</p> ") (pubDate nil "Thu, 30 Jul 2009 07:59:13 +0000")) (item nil (title nil "Christian Perrier: Amor de lejos...") (guid nil "http://www.perrier.eu.org/weblog/bubulle/planet-debian/amor") (link nil "http://www.perrier.eu.org/weblog/2009/07/30#amor") (description nil "  <img src=\"http://planet.debian.org/heads/bubulle.png\" width=\"69\" height=\"100\" alt=\"\" align=\"right\" style=\"float: right;\">  ...felices los quatro.\n<p>\nAs of today, I can now speak spanish along with my friend from\nNew-Zealand and another friend from the UK.\n</p><p>\nThat, thanks to a wonderful flamenco+beer party at Debconf. Some pictures will probably ome out soon.</p> ") (pubDate nil "Thu, 30 Jul 2009 06:50:00 +0000")) (item nil (title nil "David Wendt Jr.: apple, jailbreaking, and debconf in manhattan?!") (guid nil "tag:blogger.com,1999:blog-6645827354292489962.post-8633333034225780308") (link nil "http://dwgsoc09blog.blogspot.com/2009/07/apple-jailbreaking-and-debconf-in.html") (description nil "  <img src=\"http://planet.debian.org/heads/dwendt.png\" width=\"65\" height=\"85\" alt=\"\" align=\"right\" style=